    {
      "id": "5718c91cea0eb775c570cc719df63d4e5f670ad2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 797,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "pfarrell",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2019-08-09 14:13:08.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nWhat is libblkid and why do I suddenly need it to build Lustre?  I don't think this package is mandatory?\n\nAlso, the package is referred to in the errors as \"blkid\", but the package is actually libblkid, because we need the headers.  I've got the blkid command.\n\nSo I would say the error message is wrong & also this patch makes this previously optional package mandatory, which I'm not particularly a fan of.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "c642abc70a52364ada17c76159a7f3f6bb6fc272",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 797,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
